title: Bailte
overview: A new series of Bailte returns with Síle Nic Chonaonaigh continuing her journey through townlands across Ireland. With over 60,000 townlands in Ireland they remain one of the pillars of modern Irish life, and on this journey Síle explores the resilience within our rural communities and reveals the connection people have with their native townland and how local landscapes and traditions remain a constant influence on our lives.
